Is this 0.21 compatible?

The only thing that 0.21.x changed for parts is the depreciation of advSasModule and SASModule, used in ASAS parts and SAS parts respectively. To my understanding these still work but should be replaced with the new partmodules that provide better more evolved features.

ASAS as a concept no longer requires parts at all, and is included in all command modules, to my understanding no configuration is required for that.

SAS has been replaced with Reaction Wheels using the partModule ModuleReactionWheel.

example:


	MODULE
	{
		name = ModuleReactionWheel
		PitchTorque = 3
		YawTorque = 3
		RollTorque = 3
		RESOURCE
		{
			name = ElectricCharge
			rate = 0.3
		}
	}

TLDR; All part packs are compatible with 0.21, only plugins were broken by the update; if you want all of the new features, the small number of LLL parts impacted can easily be edited to exploit them.
Actually the old ASAS/SAS system still works for legacy parts. So you only need to edit mod parts if you want to use the new system over old system on the legacies.
